comments:
Created 18.6.1997 by renaming the parish of Seaton & 
    Downderry. See also Table 2, note (e).

The part in Devon was transferred to Cornwall on 20.10.1844. Abolished 1.4.1950 
    and added to the parish of Maker with Rame.

Created 1.4.1950 from the parishes of Maker and Rame. See also 
    Table 2, note (e).

Created 1.4.1896 out of the parish of Maker. See also Table 2, 
    note (e).

Abolished 1.4.1950 and added to the parish of Maker with 
    Rame.

Created 1.4.1997 out of the parishes of Morval, Sheviok, St. 
    Germans, St. Martin by Looe and Seaton and Downderry. Renamed 18.6.1997 to 
    become the parish of Deviock. See also Table 2, note (d).
The part in Devon was transferred to Cornwall on 20.10.1844. See also Table 2, note (e).

On 1.4.1895 the part in Devon  ecame 
    part of the parish of St. Budeaux, so that thereafter the parish of St. Stephens was wholly 
    in Cornwall. Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Saltash.

Created 1.4.1904 out of the parish of Antony. See also Table 2, 
    note (e).
